  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Defining App Components**\n\nI\'m now focusing on `src/App.tsx`, the core of the application. My current line of thinking revolves around its responsibilities: managing active state tabs like \"home\", \"search\", and \"about\", and handling current search queries and categories dynamically. I\'m considering how best to pass search parameters efficiently.\n\n\n**Implementing New Features**\n\nI\'m now integrating new features into the app. I\'m focusing on the `<AdvisorChat />` drawer\'s open/close states, and the selection of a community for tour bookings which triggers the `<BookingModal />` overlay. I plan to add an alert bar for booking confirmations and a local storage tracker for booked tours, enabling a \"My Scheduled Tours\" checklist on the home screen. I\'m re-reading `src/App.tsx` now to ensure seamless integration of these enhancements.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will edit `/src/App.tsx` to orchestrate our GoldenCare senior care application. It connects our responsive header, homepage landing sections (Hero, Stats, Care Concierge, Interior Showcase, Testimonials), the fully featured community search index, the advisor chatbot drawer, and the tour booking calendar modal. It also adds a local storage persistence engine that tracks user-scheduled tours in an elegant checklist dashboard."
